<subSubSection id="2CEF6546650F047D2AD66AD3FEE4DC83" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="264" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="644A36CD650F047C2AD66AD3FCDCDB21" blockId="14.[151,1437,1677,1812]" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="5681EADF650F047C2AD66AD3FE9DDAF9" bold="true" box="[199,315,1713,1739]" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Remarks.</emphasis>
This genus was revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="00644B3C650F047C28916AD3FC60DAF9" author="Richardson, B. J. &amp; Zabka, M." box="[640,966,1713,1742]" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" pagination="79 - 96" refId="ref13874" refString="Richardson, B. J. &amp; Zabka, M. (2007) A revision of the Australian jumping spider genus Prostheclina Keyserling, 1892 (Araneae: Salticidae). Records of the Australian Museum, 59, 79 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.59.2007.1471" type="journal article" year="2007">Richardson &amp; Żabka (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. It includes seven described species. For one species, 
<taxonomicName id="A3F54D4E650F047C2B3D6AB7FC30DADD" authority="Richardson and Zabka, 2007" authorityName="Richardson and Zabka" authorityYear="2007" box="[300,918,1749,1778]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Prostheclina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boreoaitha">
<emphasis id="5681EADF650F047C2B3D6AB7FD98DADD" box="[300,574,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Prostheclina boreoaitha</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="00644B3C650F047C28596AB7FC30DADD" author="Richardson, B. J. &amp; Zabka, M." box="[584,918,1749,1778]" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" pagination="79 - 96" refId="ref13874" refString="Richardson, B. J. &amp; Zabka, M. (2007) A revision of the Australian jumping spider genus Prostheclina Keyserling, 1892 (Araneae: Salticidae). Records of the Australian Museum, 59, 79 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.59.2007.1471" type="journal article" year="2007">Richardson and Żabka, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, only the male was described. The female is described here and the female key updated to include this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="644A36CD650E047D2A866CF5FEE4DC83" blockId="15.[151,322,151,177]" box="[151,322,151,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="264">
